    "description": "Umenohana Group Co.,Ltd. engages in the restaurant business in Japan. It operates through three segments: Restaurant, Takeout, and Outside Sale. The company offers processed marine products, such as oyster products; Furuichian rolled sushi, inari sushi, oshizushi, assorted sushi, omusubi, steamed rice, etc.; take-out bento, Japanese side dishes, new year dishes, tofu and other processed soybean products, and frozen side dishes; and gift items, as well as perishables. It also provides Yuba and Tofu Shop Ume no Hana, Japanese nabedokoro sushihan hot pot dishes, sushi, rice bowls, set meals, drinks, take-out lunch boxes, seafood izakaya sakura suisan fish dishes, grilled chicken, a la carte dishes, drinks, and other food and drink products. It offers its products under the Ume-no-Hana and Furuichian brand names. The company was formerly known as UMENOHANA Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Umenohana Group Co.,Ltd. in May 2025. Umenohana Group Co.,Ltd. was founded in 1979 and is based in Kurume, Japan."
